@startuml
title Signaling protocol (v2) — async human<->agent via Linear metadata\nsolves the HITL bottleneck (W3)

skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica

participant "Agent @flow\n(any launcher)" as A #BAFFC9
participant "Linear\n(labels · comments · reactions · webhooks)" as L
actor "Mateusz" as M #D7BAFF

== agent blocked -> signal & sleep (no interactive wait) ==
A -> L : set label needs:answer + comment (PL · MiniMax M3) + @Mateusz
A -> A : sleep / move to other task (WIP allows)
L -> M : inbox notification (webhook)

== Mateusz answers in batch (saved view) ==
M -> L : open view "needs:*" (his queue)
alt quick approve
  M -> L : react V on agent comment
else needs detail
  M -> L : comment "@flow ..." (answer)
else pause / redo
  M -> L : react X (changes) or reload (redo)
end

== webhook wakes the right agent ==
L -> A : webhook (reaction / mention / comment)
A -> L : react eyes ("received, working")
A -> L : clear needs:* ; continue work

note over A, L
  Native first: status · priority · estimate(t-shirt) ·
  relations(blocked by) · assignee(@flow) · Initiative.
  Labels only for: type:* · needs:* · risk:high · ai:* ·
  flags dor-ok/dod-ok/escalated/over-budget/transcript-uncertain.
  Emoji = micro-acks. NO custom fields (Linear has none).
end note

note right of M
  Views = control plane:
  bell My input · robot Agent working ·
  warn Attention · blocked Blocked · test Review/Test
end note
@enduml
